Use `Effect.runSync` for effects that do no async work and cannot fail. It throws synchronously if either assumption is violated.

```typescript
import { Effect, pipe } from "effect";

const program = pipe(
  Effect.succeed(10),
  Effect.map((n) => n * 2),
  Effect.map((n) => n + 1),
);

const result: number = Effect.runSync(program);
console.log(result); // 21
```

`Effect.runFork` returns a `RuntimeFiber` you can observe with `runtime.addObserver` or `Fiber.join`.

```typescript
import { Effect, Fiber, Exit } from "effect";

const work = Effect.gen(function* () {
  yield* Effect.sleep("50 millis");
  return 7 as const;
});

const fiber = Effect.runFork(work);

fiber.addObserver((exit) => {
  if (Exit.isSuccess(exit)) {
    console.log(`done with ${exit.value}`);
  } else {
    console.error("failed", exit.cause);
  }
});

// Keep type-level reference so tsc doesn't complain.
void Fiber.isFiber;
```

