Use `Effect.fork` to spawn a fiber in the parent scope, then `Fiber.join` to await the exit value inside the same `Effect.gen`.

```typescript
import { Effect, Fiber } from "effect";

const compute = Effect.succeed(42);

const program = Effect.gen(function* () {
  const fiber = yield* Effect.fork(compute);
  // ... meanwhile, do other work ...
  const value = yield* Fiber.join(fiber);
  return value + 1;
});

Effect.runPromise(program).then((n) => {
  console.log(n);
});
```

`Effect.fork` attaches the new fiber to the enclosing scope, so it gets interrupted when that scope closes. `Effect.forkDaemon` attaches it to the global scope instead, so it keeps running even if the parent finishes. You still get a `RuntimeFiber<A, E>` back, so you can `Fiber.join` or `Fiber.interrupt` it whenever you like.

```typescript
import { Effect, Fiber } from "effect";

const heartbeat = Effect.gen(function* () {
  yield* Effect.sleep("5 millis");
  return "alive" as const;
});

const parent = Effect.gen(function* () {
  const fiber = yield* Effect.forkDaemon(heartbeat);
  return fiber;
});

const main = Effect.gen(function* () {
  const fiber = yield* parent;
  const result = yield* Fiber.join(fiber);
  return result;
});

Effect.runPromise(main).then(console.log);
```

```typescript
import { Effect, Exit, Fiber } from "effect";

class PingError {
  readonly _tag = "PingError" as const;
  constructor(readonly reason: string) {}
}

const ping = (ok: boolean) =>
  ok ? Effect.succeed("pong" as const) : Effect.fail(new PingError("lost"));

const program = (ok: boolean) =>
  Effect.gen(function* () {
    const fiber = yield* Effect.forkDaemon(ping(ok));
    const exit = yield* Effect.exit(Fiber.join(fiber));
    return Exit.match(exit, {
      onSuccess: (v) => `ok:${v}`,
      onFailure: (_cause) => "failed",
    });
  });

Effect.runPromise(program(true)).then(console.log);
```

`Fiber.interrupt` sends an interruption signal and waits for the fiber to finish unwinding. A subsequent `Fiber.join` on an already-interrupted fiber yields an interrupted `Exit`.

```typescript
import { Effect, Fiber, Exit } from "effect";

const longTask = Effect.gen(function* () {
  yield* Effect.sleep("1 second");
  return "done" as const;
});

const program = Effect.gen(function* () {
  const fiber = yield* Effect.fork(longTask);
  yield* Effect.sleep("10 millis");
  yield* Fiber.interrupt(fiber);
  const exit = yield* Effect.exit(Fiber.join(fiber));
  return Exit.isInterrupted(exit) ? "interrupted" : "completed";
});

Effect.runPromise(program).then(console.log);
```

```typescript
import { Effect, Fiber } from "effect";

const ticker = Effect.gen(function* () {
  for (let i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
    yield* Effect.sleep("50 millis");
  }
  return "ticked-all" as const;
});

const interruptibleTicker = Effect.interruptible(ticker);

const program = Effect.gen(function* () {
  const fiber = yield* Effect.fork(interruptibleTicker);
  yield* Effect.sleep("80 millis");
  yield* Fiber.interrupt(fiber);
  return "parent-exited";
});

Effect.runPromise(program).then(console.log);
